        "timestamp": "2019-03-28 23:54:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Jorge, \nOriginal code break the rule of:\nCognitive Complexity of methods should not be too high\nAfter refactor if-else to ternary op, Cognitive Complexity is reduced from 31 to 17.\nI don't have strong opinion that which one is better in terms of readability.\nIn this case, only ternary op can help me remove this critical code smell.\nDo you have any other better way help solve it or we just let this code smell exist?\n\nFor your comments related to serialization, I agree, field annotated as @SerializedName should be serialized. I made a mistake, I will fix it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
